    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-11-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-11-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="803"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d803">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1115/11–1248: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Commander of the United States Naval Forces in the Western
                        Pacific</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Badger</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cabot</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="55" xml:id="d803fn55">Repeated to the Department.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tsingtao</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-11-12">November 12,
                            1948</date>.<lb/>[Received November 12—2:59 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>120803 Z. Your priority despatch 2386 of 11 November State Dept passed to me for
                    information and comment. Your request for services is all that is necessary for
                    me to provide air and/or water transportation for persons desiring to leave
                    China for security reasons. Please inform my designated representative, Rear
                    Admiral Entwistle, and me if you like, of your requirements in terms of what you
                    need and when you need it. Our agreed plans already cover shuttle service to
                    Japan where CinCFE<note n="56" xml:id="d803fn56">Commander in Chief, Far East
                        (MacArthur).</note> stands ready at my request to receive and care for
                    evacuees and to make arrangements for their onward routing to US. I only await
                    the necessary information to begin the transportation of these individuals.</p>
                <p>With regard to the gasoline, I stand ready to render assistance in this regard in
                    case needs for evacuation purposes can be justified as differentiated from the
                    routine operation of commercial airlines. Agree with you that all US nationals
                    now desiring to leave area should have transportation provided now and passage
                    facilitated as much as possible.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
